04:37.451 --> 04:39.104
-[KIDS ALL TALK AT ONCE]

04:39.235 --> 04:42.673
-OKAY, VERY FUNNY,
HA HA, ONE AT A TIME.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.285
-I'M GETTING MY
EARS PIERCED, MAN,

04:45.415 --> 04:47.765
AS SOON AS TRYOUTS ARE OVER,
I DON'T CARE WHAT MY DAD SAYS.

04:47.896 --> 04:49.637
-OH COME ON, HOBIE, EVERYONE
CARES WHAT YOUR DAD SAYS.

04:49.767 --> 04:52.335
-THE ONLY QUESTION IS:
ONE EAR OR TWO?

04:52.466 --> 04:54.772
-FORGET THE EAR, MAN,
DO YOUR BELLY BUTTON.

04:54.903 --> 04:55.686
-OOH!

04:55.817 --> 04:56.731
-MAYBE AN EYEBROW.

04:56.861 --> 04:58.298
-NO, NO, GET YOUR TONGUE.

04:58.428 --> 05:00.691
-YOU SHOULD GET YOUR
LIPS PIERCED TOGETHER.

05:00.822 --> 05:02.954
-[LAUGHS] LET'S GO.

05:07.350 --> 05:11.659
-[KIDS AND LIFEGUARD TALKING]

05:21.364 --> 05:22.278
-OKAY, NEXT?

05:23.714 --> 05:26.108
-HEY, AM I TOO LATE
FOR THE TRYOUTS?

05:26.238 --> 05:29.372
-UH, NO, BUT THESE ARE
JUNIOR LIFEGUARD TRYOUTS.

05:29.503 --> 05:30.895
-YEAH, RIGHT, RIGHT?

05:31.722 --> 05:33.245
-HOW OLD ARE YOU?

05:33.376 --> 05:35.335
-SEVENTEEN, I MEAN I WANNA
BE A REGULAR LIFEGUARD,

05:35.465 --> 05:38.468
YOU KNOW, A WORKING LIFEGUARD
BUT THEY SAID I HAVE TO BE 18.

05:38.599 --> 05:40.035
-CODY: THAT'S RIGHT.

05:40.165 --> 05:41.689
-THEN I GUESS THIS
IS WHAT I NEED TO DO.

05:43.778 --> 05:45.127
-YOU EVER DONE THE BUOY SWIM?

05:45.257 --> 05:47.651
-BUOY SWIM? NO, NOT REALLY.

05:47.782 --> 05:50.045
I MEAN WE JUST MOVED TO
MALIBU FROM RIVERSIDE.

05:50.175 --> 05:52.961
I SWAM IN POOLS A LOT,
I CAN SWIM TEN TIMES

05:53.091 --> 05:55.093
THAT FAR AND NOT EVEN
GET OUT OF BREATH.

05:55.224 --> 05:57.139
-THE OCEAN'S QUITE A BIT
DIFFERENT THAN A POOL.

05:57.269 --> 05:59.750
-OH I KNOW, BUT I LOVE IT HERE.

05:59.881 --> 06:01.665
I MEAN, THE BEACH IS
WHERE I WANNA WORK.

06:01.796 --> 06:03.624
I WANNA BE A LIFEGUARD,

06:03.754 --> 06:05.408
KEEP PEOPLE SAFE
WHEN THEY COME HERE.

06:06.496 --> 06:07.889
-WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

06:08.019 --> 06:10.674
-MANUEL GUTIERREZ,
PEOPLE CALL ME MANNY.

06:10.805 --> 06:14.635
-CODY MADISON, WELL, MANNY,
THANKS FOR COMING OUT.

06:17.899 --> 06:19.335
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

06:19.466 --> 06:20.858
GO STRETCH, GET
READY FOR THE SWIM.

06:20.989 --> 06:22.556
-HEY MAN, THANKS A LOT, THANKS!

06:23.557 --> 06:25.820
-YOU GOT IT, ALL RIGHT,
EVERYBODY ELSE, FOLLOW HIM,

06:25.950 --> 06:27.865
LINE UP AT THE FLAGS,
LET'S GO, HUP, HUP, HUP!

06:36.570 --> 06:37.658
ALL RIGHT, LINE IT UP!

06:54.414 --> 06:56.328
-C.J.: HI, IS
THERE ANYTHING WRONG?

06:56.459 --> 06:57.982
-THAT MAN OVER THERE'S CRAZY!

06:58.113 --> 06:59.375
HE SHOULD BE LOCKED AWAY.

07:00.594 --> 07:02.117
-WHAT DID HE DO?

07:02.247 --> 07:03.771
-HE TRIED TO GIVE MY LITTLE
GIRL ONE OF THOSE RAGS

07:03.901 --> 07:06.295
OFF HIS CART, WE KEPT WALKING
BUT HE CHASED AFTER US

07:06.948 --> 07:09.211
AND HE KEPT TRYING TO FORCE
HER TO TAKE IT FROM HIM.

07:09.341 --> 07:10.778
-DID HE HURT EITHER ONE OF YOU?

07:10.908 --> 07:12.736
-NO, THANK GOD, BUT
WHO KNOWS WHERE THOSE

07:12.867 --> 07:15.478
FILTHY RAGS HAVE BEEN OR
WHAT THEY'VE BEEN SOAKED IN.

07:16.087 --> 07:18.046
I MEAN, WHY CAN'T YOU KEEP
PEOPLE LIKE THAT OFF THE BEACH?

07:18.176 --> 07:20.222
-I'M SORRY, IT'S A
PUBLIC BEACH, MA'AM.

07:20.352 --> 07:21.441
BUT I'LL GO TALK TO HIM.

07:24.095 --> 07:25.706
ENJOY THE REST OF YOUR DAY.

07:29.492 --> 07:33.540
-[STRAINING]

07:47.858 --> 07:49.033
-HELLO.

07:49.686 --> 07:50.600
CAN I HELP YOU WITH THAT?

07:50.731 --> 07:51.775
-WHY?

07:52.341 --> 07:54.038
-WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE
YOU COULD USE SOME HELP.

07:54.561 --> 07:58.652
-IS THAT SO? THEN WHY
HASN'T ANYONE STOPPED?

07:58.782 --> 08:00.958
-WELL, SOMEBODY HAS.

08:01.089 --> 08:03.134
NOW ARE WE GONNA PUSH THIS
ON THE BIKE PATH OR NOT?

08:04.832 --> 08:06.311
-THINK YOU'RE STRONG ENOUGH?

08:06.442 --> 08:09.663
-WELL, WE'LL SOON FIND
OUT, READY? ON THREE.

08:10.968 --> 08:13.362
ONE, TWO THREE!

08:18.323 --> 08:19.673
THERE YOU GO!

08:20.630 --> 08:21.805
WE DID IT!

08:21.936 --> 08:23.894
-BIKER: HEY, WATCH IT, MAN!

08:24.025 --> 08:26.331
-GO AROUND! GO AROUND!

08:27.942 --> 08:29.291
-YOU KNOW WHAT, I
THINK THIS WOULD BE

08:29.421 --> 08:31.380
SAFER OFF THE BIKE
PATH, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

08:33.991 --> 08:34.861
-OVER THERE.

08:34.991 --> 08:35.993
-OKAY.

08:36.124 --> 08:37.865
-AH, AH AH. I CAN HANDLE IT!

08:39.475 --> 08:42.957
BUT YOU CAN MEET ME OVER
THERE IF YOU WANT TO.

09:09.026 --> 09:11.986
HERE, GO AHEAD TAKE IT.

09:12.116 --> 09:13.944
-OH, THANK YOU.

09:15.163 --> 09:17.426
-YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THANKING ME FOR.

09:18.166 --> 09:19.559
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT IS?

09:19.689 --> 09:20.690
-IT'S A SATIN, ISN'T IT?

09:21.386 --> 09:25.129
-IT'S SILK CHARMEUSE,
CUT ALONG THE BIAS.

09:25.739 --> 09:26.740
DO YOU KNOW WHERE IT CAME FROM?

09:26.870 --> 09:28.611
-NO.

09:28.742 --> 09:31.005
-IT'S PART OF JEAN
HARLOW'S DRESS.

09:31.658 --> 09:33.660
SHE WORE IN DINNER AT EIGHT.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.575
HOLD IT CLOSE TO YOURSELF.

09:36.750 --> 09:37.664
FEEL IT!

09:38.882 --> 09:44.322
CAN YOU FEEL HER PASSION
OF LIFE IN EVERY FIBER?

09:44.453 --> 09:46.586
-ARE YOU SURE THIS IS PART
OF JEAN HARLOW'S DRESS?

09:48.196 --> 09:51.765
-THIS IS THE FABRIC
OF HISTORY, THE FABRIC

09:51.895 --> 09:54.245
OF HOLLYWOOD IN IT'S GLORY DAYS.

09:54.855 --> 09:57.727
SHIRLEY TEMPLE IN CURLY TOP.

09:58.598 --> 10:00.251
ROBERT MITCHUM IN THE BIG SLEEP.

10:02.906 --> 10:05.387
JANE RUSSELL IN THE OUTLAW.

10:07.258 --> 10:08.520
-NOW WHERE DID
YOU GET ALL OF THESE?

10:09.870 --> 10:11.436
-NO ONE REMEMBERS.

10:14.614 --> 10:15.745
I AM MAX MARAT.

10:17.268 --> 10:20.097
I DID THE WARDROBE
FOR THE GREAT STARS.

10:22.273 --> 10:25.407
THESE ARE MY CREATIONS.

10:28.279 --> 10:30.717
-OKAY, THE QUALIFYING
TIME IS THREE MINUTES,

10:30.847 --> 10:32.675
AROUND THE BUOY
AND BACK TO SHORE.

10:32.806 --> 10:34.024
IF YOU DON'T MAKE IT TODAY,

10:34.155 --> 10:35.678
YOU CAN TRY ONE
MORE TIME TOMORROW.

10:36.418 --> 10:38.115
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY READY?

10:39.029 --> 10:40.248
GET SET!

10:41.684 --> 10:43.077
[BLOWS WHISTLE] GO!

10:50.519 --> 10:52.086
THOSE KIDS ARE PRETTY FAST.

10:54.001 --> 10:55.132
-ALL RIGHT, COME
ON GUYS, LET'S GO!

10:55.263 --> 10:56.960
KEEP IT MOVING, KEEP IT MOVING!

11:24.335 --> 11:25.728
SWIMMER DOWN!

11:26.511 --> 11:28.992
-HERE TAKE THIS,
WATCH THE KIDS, GO!

11:42.397 --> 11:46.706
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

12:01.198 --> 12:02.460
-DON'T WORRY! I GOT YOU!

12:02.591 --> 12:03.984
-MANNY: WHAT ARE YOU DOING MAN

12:04.506 --> 12:05.986
-HOBIE: YOU WENT UNDER WATER!

12:06.595 --> 12:08.553
-I SWIM FASTER UNDER WATER!

12:10.425 --> 12:11.339
-ARE YOU GUYS OKAY?

12:11.469 --> 12:12.688
-MAN, HE GOT IN MY WAY.

12:12.819 --> 12:13.994
-I THOUGHT HE WAS DROWNING.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.213
-MANNY: MAN, I
WASN'T DROWNING!

12:39.976 --> 12:41.369
-HI LOGAN.
-LOGAN: HEY

12:41.499 --> 12:42.892
-HOW'S THAT GUY WE DUG OUT?
DID HE MAKE IT?

12:43.023 --> 12:44.633
-YEAH, WE REVIVED HIM ON
THE WAY TO THE HOSPITAL.

12:44.764 --> 12:46.243
THE DOCTOR SAID
HE SHOULD BE FINE.

12:46.374 --> 12:47.375
WHAT'S THAT?

12:48.593 --> 12:50.857
-OH, IT'S A PIECE OF
JEAN HARLOW'S DRESS.

12:51.858 --> 12:53.685
-DON'T TELL ME, YOU MET
UP WITH THE RAG MAN TODAY.

12:53.816 --> 12:56.079
-WELL, IF YOU MEAN
MAX MURAT, YES.

12:57.080 --> 12:58.908
DON'T YOU REALIZE HE'S A
FAMOUS COSTUME DESIGNER

12:59.039 --> 13:00.780
FROM THE GOLDEN
ERA OF HOLLYWOOD?

13:00.910 --> 13:02.694
-C.J., HE'S A LUNATIC WHO'S
IN AND OUT OF MENTAL HOSPITALS.

13:02.825 --> 13:04.392
HE FINDS RAGS IN DUMPSTERS AND

13:04.522 --> 13:05.523
PUTS THEM ON THAT CART OF HIS.

13:05.654 --> 13:07.047
-YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

13:07.177 --> 13:09.005
-I'VE SEEN HIM, C.J., I KNOW.

13:10.311 --> 13:11.138
-ARE YOU SURE?

13:11.268 --> 13:12.182
-POSITIVE.

13:15.533 --> 13:16.665
-HE SEEMS SO GENUINE.

13:17.492 --> 13:19.015
-HE'S TOTALLY BONKERS.

13:19.146 --> 13:20.321
THIS IS PROBABLY
PART OF A PILLOW CASE

13:20.451 --> 13:21.539
SOMEBODY THREW AWAY.

13:22.366 --> 13:24.238
ANYWAY, SEE YA.

13:54.094 --> 13:55.835
-HOBIE: THAT'S NOT FAIR,
WHY DO I HAVE TO

13:55.965 --> 13:57.401
TEACH HIM HOW TO
SWIM IN THE OCEAN?

13:57.532 --> 13:59.839
-BECAUSE YOU'RE A JUNIOR
LIFEGUARD INSTRUCTOR.

14:00.665 --> 14:02.711
-I DIDN'T EVEN WANT TO DO
JUNIOR GUARDS THIS SUMMER.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.540
-SO YOU SAID, BUT MANNY
DOES, ENOUGH TO TRY OUT

14:05.670 --> 14:08.325
WITHOUT ANY OCEAN
EXPERIENCE, WHICH YOU HAVE

14:08.456 --> 14:11.198
AND COULD SHARE WITH HIM IF
YOU WEREN'T BEING SO SELFISH.

14:11.328 --> 14:14.549
-DAD, C'MON, YOU KNOW I DO A
LOT OF STUFF FOR OTHER PEOPLE.

14:14.679 --> 14:17.117
YOU JUST DON'T LIKE IT WHEN I
WANNA DO SOMETHING FOR MYSELF.

14:17.247 --> 14:19.597
-WHAT'S MORE IMPORTANT
FOR YOU TO DO FOR YOURSELF

14:19.728 --> 14:21.164
THAN TO HELP THAT BOY ACCOMPLISH

14:21.295 --> 14:23.079
SOMETHING THAT'S VERY
IMPORTANT TO HIM?

14:23.993 --> 14:25.473
-I MADE PLANS TO DO SOMETHING

14:25.603 --> 14:27.301
IMPORTANT WITH J.B. AND CONNOR.

14:27.431 --> 14:28.911
-WHAT?

14:29.042 --> 14:30.260
-I DON'T KNOW, WE WERE,
WE WERE GONNA GO DOWN

14:30.391 --> 14:32.959
TO VENICE AND CHECK
OUT SOME STUFF.

14:34.525 --> 14:37.528
SO YOU KNOW WHAT, JUST
FORGET IT, FINE, YOU WIN.

14:38.225 --> 14:40.488
I'LL TEACH HIM HOW
TO SWIM, YOU HAPPY?

14:41.097 --> 14:45.232
-I'M THRILLED, HOBSTER,
I'M ABSOLUTELY THRILLED.

14:48.844 --> 14:50.628
-CODY: YOU'LL BE
FINE, ALL RIGHT?

14:50.759 --> 14:52.239
-HOBIE: HEY C'MON, BUDDY,
LET'S GO, YOU READY?

14:52.369 --> 14:53.718
-MANNY: YEAH.

14:53.849 --> 14:55.372
-CODY: ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

14:56.678 --> 14:59.159
-NOT EASY BEING THE PARENT
OF A 16-YEAR-OLD, IS IT?

14:59.289 --> 15:02.162
-IT'S NOT EASY BEING A
16-YEAR-OLD THESE DAYS EITHER.

15:02.814 --> 15:05.208
-THAT'S WHAT I LOVE ABOUT
YOU, MITCH, YOUR EMPATHY.

15:05.339 --> 15:08.603
YOU CARE ABOUT WHAT OTHER
PEOPLE WANT, WHAT THEY NEED.

15:08.733 --> 15:12.215
-[LAUGHS] YOU'RE NOT
GETTING MY DAY OFF.

15:12.824 --> 15:14.043
-PLEASE, MITCH, SWITCH WITH ME.

15:14.174 --> 15:15.784
I HAVE A REALLY
IMPORTANT APPOINTMENT.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.307
-I'M SO SORRY.

15:18.526 --> 15:20.093
-BUT I LOVE YOU, MAN.

15:20.223 --> 15:22.617
-I LOVE YOU TOO, BUT YOU'RE
NOT GETTING MY DAY OFF.

15:28.971 --> 15:31.365
-JOHN! I NEED TO
TALK TO YOU, BUDDY.

15:34.411 --> 15:36.109
-ALL RIGHT, NOW
DON'T KICK SO HARD.

15:36.239 --> 15:38.720
KICKING'S ONLY FOR
FLOTATION NOT PROPULSION.

15:42.202 --> 15:43.246
THERE YOU GO!

15:48.773 --> 15:50.732
ALL RIGHT, NOW DON'T OVERREACH.

15:50.862 --> 15:54.388
PUT YOUR HAND IN THE
WATER BEFORE YOUR
ARM'S FULLY EXTENDED.

15:54.518 --> 15:57.521
DON'T CUP YOUR HANDS SO MUCH,
IT ONLY MAKES THEM SMALLER.

15:58.392 --> 16:00.176
THERE YOU GO, THAT'S BETTER.

16:00.829 --> 16:03.223
ALL RIGHT, NOW TRY PUTTING
YOUR FACE IN THE WATER.

16:03.353 --> 16:05.007
BREATHE ON EVERY RIGHT STROKE.

16:07.096 --> 16:10.273
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S
BETTER, YOU GOT IT.

16:10.404 --> 16:13.102
YOU'RE GONNA BE A
LIFEGUARD IN NO TIME, YEAH!

16:20.675 --> 16:21.676
-MAX?

16:22.982 --> 16:24.244
MAX?
-MAX: WHAT?

16:29.249 --> 16:30.424
CATCHING SOME WINKS.

16:32.078 --> 16:33.470
-I'M SORRY, I DIDN'T
MEAN TO WAKE YOU.

16:33.601 --> 16:35.255
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE
SURE YOU'RE OKAY.

16:37.257 --> 16:38.345
-HAVE YOU A NAME?

16:38.475 --> 16:39.955
-OH, IT'S C.J.

16:40.086 --> 16:43.567
-C.J.? THOSE ARE
INITIALS, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

16:44.916 --> 16:46.222
-WELL, IT'S CASEY JEAN.

16:47.528 --> 16:49.138
BUT I'VE BEEN CALLED
C.J. SINCE I WAS LITTLE.

16:49.269 --> 16:50.922
-AH.

16:51.053 --> 16:52.402
-I HAVE SOME COFFEE IN THE
TRUCK IF YOU'D LIKE SOME.

16:53.621 --> 16:56.015
-GLORIA SWANSON USED
TO BRING ME IRISH COFFEE

16:56.145 --> 16:57.799
WHEN WE DID SUNSET BOULEVARD.

16:57.929 --> 17:00.280
-WELL, IT'S JUST PLAIN,
OLD AMERICAN, BUT IT'S HOT.

17:10.550 --> 17:12.291
I HAVE A BLUEBERRY MUFFIN,
TOO, IF YOU'RE HUNGRY.

17:12.422 --> 17:15.164
-HAVE YOU EVER DINED WITH A MAN

17:15.295 --> 17:17.384
OF WEALTH AND FAME, CASEY JEAN?

17:18.079 --> 17:19.167
-NO, I'M AFRAID NOT.

17:20.778 --> 17:23.259
-BE AFRAID NO LONGER.

17:36.664 --> 17:39.797
I FOUGHT TO PRODUCE
MOTION PICTURES THAT WOULD

17:39.928 --> 17:43.062
ELEVATE THE SPIRIT AND
INSPIRE THE SOUL BUT...

17:44.324 --> 17:46.717
THE STUDIO HACKS
DESTROYED EVERYONE.

17:48.067 --> 17:50.982
HOLD TIGHT TO YOUR
DREAMS, CASEY JEAN.

17:52.071 --> 17:54.421
SO TIGHT NO ONE
CAN PRY THEM LOOSE.

17:57.772 --> 18:00.818
-NOW, I THOUGHT YOU WERE A
COSTUME DESIGNER,
NOT A PRODUCER.

18:00.949 --> 18:03.430
-I DID IT ALL,
EVERY JOB. [LAUGHS]

18:03.560 --> 18:06.346
THE STUDIO STILL PESTERS
ME TO COME BACK TO WORK

18:06.476 --> 18:10.263
BUT I'M MUCH TOO BUSY--
MUCH TOO BUSY COLLECTING.

18:11.307 --> 18:13.179
-WELL, SPEAKING OF WORK, I HAVE

18:13.309 --> 18:15.006
TO GO ON DUTY IN FIVE MINUTES.

18:16.791 --> 18:20.751
-JOHNNY WEISSMULLER WORE
THIS IN TARZAN THE APEMAN.

18:21.491 --> 18:23.102
JOHNNY WAS A LIFEGUARD,
YOU KNOW.

18:23.232 --> 18:25.582
HE WORKED RIGHT HERE
ON VENICE BEACH.

18:28.846 --> 18:30.500
-SO HOW DID YOU END
UP LIVING HERE, MAX?

18:31.545 --> 18:32.676
-LUCKY, I GUESS.

18:33.677 --> 18:36.027
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
THE SLEEVE OF THE BLOUSE

18:36.158 --> 18:39.074
MARILYN MONROE WORE
IN SOME LIKE IT HOT?

18:41.381 --> 18:44.253
-WELL, MAYBE NEXT TIME,
I GOTTA GET TO WORK.

18:44.384 --> 18:45.994
DO YOU NEED ANY MONEY OR
ANYTHING FOR A PLACE TO STAY?

18:46.125 --> 18:50.129
-NO, NO MONEY, OH MY
GOODNESS, I DON'T NEED MONEY,

18:50.259 --> 18:53.654
BUT IT'S VERY NICE
OF YOU TO OFFER.

18:55.221 --> 18:56.657
-OH, MAX, YOU OKAY?

18:57.832 --> 18:59.616
-FINE, I'M FINE.

19:01.052 --> 19:03.925
I JUST GET THIS LITTLE
FLUTTER IN MY HEART

19:04.055 --> 19:06.797
WHENEVER I'M AROUND SUCH BEAUTY.

19:07.450 --> 19:09.496
LANA TURNER DID THE
SAME THING TO ME.

19:09.626 --> 19:11.498
I'VE GOT ONE OF
HER STOCKINGS FROM

19:11.628 --> 19:13.456
THE POSTMAN ALWAYS RINGS TWICE.

19:14.544 --> 19:18.026
IT'S ON THE CART SOME
PLACE, I'LL FIND IT,

19:18.157 --> 19:21.421
SHOW IT TO YOU NEXT
TIME WE MEET AND VISIT.

19:23.597 --> 19:25.294
-OKAY, SEE YOU LATER, MAX.

19:25.425 --> 19:27.557
-GOODBYE, CASEY JEAN.

19:27.688 --> 19:31.779
-[GENTLE GUITAR MUSIC]

19:38.655 --> 19:43.834
-[ROCK MUSIC]

19:49.405 --> 19:50.580
-THAT WAS GREAT.

19:53.453 --> 19:56.934
HEY THANKS, MAN, REALLY,
YOU KNOW YOUR STUFF.

19:57.587 --> 19:59.763
-SO, DO YOU LIVE IN THE COLONY?

19:59.894 --> 20:01.635
-THE WHAT?

20:01.765 --> 20:04.507
-YOU KNOW, THE MALIBU COLONY,
THE ENCLAVE OF THE STARS?

20:04.638 --> 20:06.422
-OH, YOU MEAN BEHIND THE GATES.

20:07.554 --> 20:09.033
YEAH, THAT'S WHERE WE LIVE.

20:09.643 --> 20:11.297
-SO, WHAT DO YOUR PARENTS DO?

20:12.254 --> 20:13.777
-WELL, MY MOM'S A MAID.

20:15.997 --> 20:17.433
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

20:17.564 --> 20:19.870
-WE LIVE IN A GUEST
HOUSE, BUT IT'S COOL.

20:20.001 --> 20:22.438
I MEAN, MY MOM, MAN, SHE
LOVES IT AT THE BEACH, TOO.

20:23.483 --> 20:25.180
-WHERE'S YOUR DAD?

20:25.311 --> 20:28.836
-THE INS DEPORTED HIM, BUT
HE'LL MAKE IT BACK UP HERE SOON.

20:29.924 --> 20:31.534
-YOU'RE NOT AMERICAN CITIZENS?

20:31.665 --> 20:34.320
-I AM, MAN, I WAS BORN HERE?

20:36.365 --> 20:38.324
SO, WHY DON'T YOU
WANNA BE A LIFEGUARD?

20:39.020 --> 20:41.588
I MEAN, WHAT BETTER
JOB IS THERE?

20:41.718 --> 20:43.154
-I DON'T KNOW.

20:44.112 --> 20:45.940
I THINK I WANT TO BE A MUSICIAN.

20:46.070 --> 20:49.378
I MEAN, MY DAD'S A
LIFEGUARD, THAT'S HIS THING.

20:49.509 --> 20:51.293
-WHAT'S UP, BUCHANNON?
-WHAT'S UP, GUYS?

20:51.424 --> 20:52.338
-WHAT'S UP, MAN,
YOU STILL GONNA DO IT

20:52.468 --> 20:53.252
OR YOU GONNA BE A WUSS?

20:53.382 --> 20:54.470
-DUDE, I'M DOING IT.

20:55.166 --> 20:56.603
-DOING WHAT?

20:56.733 --> 20:58.169
-BODY PIERCING UP IN
VENICE, YOU WANNA GO?

20:58.300 --> 21:02.261
-VENICE? I'VE NEVER
BEEN IN VENICE, SURE!

21:02.391 --> 21:06.700
-[AFRICAN MUSIC]

23:02.555 --> 23:06.515
-[TATTOO NEEDLE BUZZING]

23:23.619 --> 23:24.881
-THAT'S WHAT I'M GONNA GET.

23:27.797 --> 23:28.624
-PIERCED MAN: THAT'S
FOR YOUR TONGUE.

23:31.453 --> 23:32.933
-DOES IT HURT?

23:33.063 --> 23:34.717
-NO, NOT AT ALL,
ACTUALLY, IT'S REALLY COOL.

23:34.848 --> 23:36.502
I MEAN, YOU KNOW, EVERYBODY
GETS THEIR EARS PIERCED.

23:36.632 --> 23:39.635
IF YOU REALLY WANT TO MAKE
A STATEMENT, THAT'S IT, MAN.

23:46.425 --> 23:47.556
-YOU GONNA DO IT?

24:00.874 --> 24:02.615
-CODY: WHAT ARE
YOU THINKING ABOUT?

24:02.745 --> 24:05.313
-C.J.: I'M JUST THINKING
ABOUT MAX, YOU KNOW, THAT GUY

24:05.444 --> 24:07.358
THAT GAVE ME A PIECE
OF JEAN HARLOW'S DRESS?

24:08.359 --> 24:10.231
-I THOUGHT LOGAN
SAID HE WAS A NUTCASE.

24:10.361 --> 24:12.581
-OH, I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE HE IS.

24:12.712 --> 24:15.192
MAYBE YOU ARE, MAYBE ONE
DAY YOU'LL FIND YOURSELF

24:15.323 --> 24:16.585
WALKING DOWN THE
BEACH DROOLING AND

24:16.716 --> 24:18.500
MUTTERING I WAS
ALMOST AN OLYMPIAN.

24:18.631 --> 24:21.590
-YEAH, RIGHT, THANKS FOR THE
CONFIDENCE IN MY FUTURE, C.J.

24:21.721 --> 24:23.679
-I'LL STICK BY
YOU NO MATTER WHAT.

24:26.116 --> 24:28.118
-EVEN IF NEELY AND
I BECOME PARTNERS?

24:29.119 --> 24:32.819
-YOU AND SNEELY,
PARTNERS? IN WHAT?

24:32.949 --> 24:35.604
-IN A BUSINESS,
IT'S A GREAT IDEA.

24:35.735 --> 24:37.606
WHAT DO ICE SKATERS
DO AFTER THE OLYMPICS?

24:37.737 --> 24:39.565
THEY DO ICE SHOW EXTRAVAGANZAS.

24:39.695 --> 24:42.219
GYMNASTS ARE MAKING A FORTUNE
DOING INTERNATIONAL TOURS.

24:42.350 --> 24:43.743
BUT WHAT ABOUT WATER SPORTS?

24:43.873 --> 24:45.527
HOW DO SWIMMERS AND
DIVERS TURN PRO?

24:45.658 --> 24:47.442
-YOU MEAN BESIDES
BECOMING A LIFEGUARD?

24:47.573 --> 24:50.053
-EXACTLY, THEY DON'T,
SO NEELY AND I WANT TO

24:50.184 --> 24:52.752
FORM A WATER SHOW
SPECTACULAR, HIGH-DIVERS,

24:52.882 --> 24:54.928
SYNCHRONIZED SWIMMING, WATER
BALLET, HUGE PRODUCTION

24:55.058 --> 24:57.539
NUMBERS, FIREWORKS,
EVERYTHING GOING ON.

24:57.670 --> 24:59.236
-YOU AND NEELY?

24:59.367 --> 25:01.674
-I KNOW, IT'S CRAZY,
IT WAS HER IDEA.

25:02.718 --> 25:04.024
-WELL, IT'S A PRETTY GOOD IDEA.

25:05.416 --> 25:07.201
-NOW WE JUST NEED
TO FIND INVESTORS.

25:07.331 --> 25:09.159
-WELL, JUST KEEP YOUR
EYES OPEN FOR NEELY.

25:09.290 --> 25:10.987
SHE HAS HER OWN WAY
OF DOING BUSINESS.

25:11.118 --> 25:13.250
-YEAH, I'M ON TOP
OF IT, DON'T WORRY.

25:13.381 --> 25:15.775
-I NEVER WORRY,
LIFE'S TOO SHORT.

25:17.690 --> 25:19.648
-COME WITH ME TO THE
PASADENA POOL THIS WEEKEND.

25:19.779 --> 25:21.824
WE'RE HOLDING TRYOUTS, YOU
CAN SEE WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT.

25:22.912 --> 25:25.524
-OKAY, BUT I ALREADY
KNOW WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT.

25:26.437 --> 25:27.613
IT'S ABOUT YOU AND ME.

25:33.836 --> 25:37.144
LIFEGUARD: OKAY, KIDS, STRETCH
UP OVER YOUR HEAD.

25:37.274 --> 25:39.712
GOOD, REACH UP THERE.

25:41.104 --> 25:43.019
-MANNY, MANNY!

25:43.759 --> 25:46.283
RELAX, MAN, SAVE YOUR
ENERGY, ALL RIGHT?

25:46.414 --> 25:50.157
OKAY, NOW JUST VISUALIZE THE
COURSE AND STUDY THE WAVES.

25:51.071 --> 25:53.160
OKAY?
-ALL RIGHT.

25:54.422 --> 25:57.207
LIFEGUARD: GOOD. ALL RIGHT,
EASY NOW.

25:57.730 --> 26:00.907
OVER YOUR HEAD. REACH UP.

26:01.037 --> 26:02.604
REACHING.

26:02.735 --> 26:04.954
VERY GOOD.

26:05.085 --> 26:08.479
ALL RIGHT, RIGHT ARM.
GOOD, YEAH.

26:13.702 --> 26:15.356
CHANGE ARM, LEFT.

26:17.706 --> 26:18.881
VERY GOOD.

26:19.926 --> 26:22.668
-LOOKING GOOD! HEY GUYS!

26:22.798 --> 26:23.669
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:23.799 --> 26:25.061
-WHERE'S THE HOBSTER?

26:25.192 --> 26:26.193
-DIDN'T SHOW UP,
DID HE SAY HE WAS

26:26.323 --> 26:27.455
COMING DOWN HERE THIS MORNING?

26:28.456 --> 26:30.589
-WELL, HE SLEPT AT
CONNOR'S LAST NIGHT.

26:31.590 --> 26:32.895
-I'LL ASK CONNOR FOR YOU.

26:33.026 --> 26:34.854
HEY, MITCH, MIND
IF I SAY SOMETHING?

26:34.984 --> 26:36.290
-SURE, WHAT?

26:36.420 --> 26:38.248
-NOBODY'S CALLED
HOBIE "THE HOBSTER"

26:38.379 --> 26:40.642
SINCE HE WAS 12 EXCEPT YOU.

26:40.773 --> 26:42.688
HE'S GROWING UP, MITCH, BUT
YOU'RE STILL STUCK IN THE PAST.

26:42.818 --> 26:44.777
-I'M NOT STUCK IN THE PAST.

26:44.907 --> 26:46.648
-YOU'RE STUCK IN THE PAST.

26:46.779 --> 26:48.824
YOU BECAME A PRIVATE EYE BUT
YOU WON'T QUIT LIFEGUARDING.

26:48.955 --> 26:50.565
CODY, I'LL NEVER QUIT
LIFEGUARDING, I'M JUST

26:50.696 --> 26:53.394
DOING SOMETHING
IN ADDITION TO IT.

26:53.524 --> 26:55.918
-AND THAT'S ALL
HOBIE WANTS TO DO.

26:57.616 --> 26:59.356
I'LL ASK CONNOR WHERE HE WENT.

27:00.140 --> 27:00.923
-THANKS.

27:01.054 --> 27:01.924
-YEAH.

27:06.015 --> 27:08.322
-STUCK IN THE PAST.

27:10.759 --> 27:11.804
-CONNOR!

27:17.331 --> 27:18.985
-HEY MANNY, THAT'S GOOD!

27:19.115 --> 27:20.856
CHECKING FOR INSHORE HOLES, HUH?

27:22.597 --> 27:25.252
-YEAH, I KNOW, HOBIE TAUGHT ME.

27:25.382 --> 27:26.166
HE'S YOUR SON, RIGHT?

27:26.296 --> 27:27.950
-YEAH.

27:28.081 --> 27:29.648
-WHAT A GREAT GUY, YOU
MUST BE REALLY PROUD OF HIM.

27:29.778 --> 27:32.085
-I AM AND YOUR PARENTS
MUST BE REALLY PROUD OF YOU.

27:32.215 --> 27:34.957
-WELL, THEY WILL BE WHEN
I BECOME A LIFEGUARD.

27:35.088 --> 27:37.177
-THAT WHY YOU WANT TO
BE A LIFEGUARD SO BADLY?

27:37.307 --> 27:40.049
-THAT'S PART OF IT, BUT,
I MEAN, I SEE TOO MANY

27:40.180 --> 27:43.749
PEOPLE WASTING UP THEIR
LIVES, WASTING EACH OTHER.

27:43.879 --> 27:46.447
ME, I WANNA SAVE LIVES.

27:46.577 --> 27:48.231
I WANNA BECOME A LIFEGUARD.

27:48.362 --> 27:50.843
-MANNY, I CAN'T THINK
OF A BETTER REASON.

27:50.973 --> 27:54.498
-OKAY, OKAY, LET'S GO,
EVERYBODY LINE UP, LET'S DO IT!

27:55.238 --> 27:57.153
-GOOD LUCK TO YOU,
I KNOW YOU'LL MAKE IT

27:57.284 --> 27:59.286
-WELL, IF I DO,
I OWE IT TO HOBIE.

27:59.416 --> 28:01.941
AND YOU, YOU RAISED HIM.

28:05.292 --> 28:07.207
-HEY MITCH, CONNOR SAID HE WENT

28:07.337 --> 28:09.078
TO THE TATTOO PARLOR IN VENICE.

28:14.475 --> 28:19.698
-[SIREN BLARES]

28:24.006 --> 28:25.660
-TWO-NINE-FIVE FROM UNIT THREE.

28:26.182 --> 28:29.577
I NEED A CALL CAR AT VENICE
STRAND CLOSE TO TOWER 27.

28:29.708 --> 28:30.665
CODE THREE.

28:39.587 --> 28:41.110
EXCUSE ME.

28:41.981 --> 28:42.895
WHAT HAPPENED?

28:43.025 --> 28:44.070
-HE COLLAPSED. I SAW HIM.

28:44.200 --> 28:45.201
HE WAS HOLDING HIS CHEST.

28:45.332 --> 28:46.637
IT LOOKED LIKE A HEART ATTACK.

28:49.423 --> 28:50.424
-HE'S NOT BREATHING.

28:50.554 --> 28:52.165
MAX, COME ON!

28:53.340 --> 28:54.254
BREATHE!

28:54.384 --> 28:57.823
-[SIREN BLARES]

29:05.613 --> 29:06.570
-WHAT DO WE GOT?

29:06.701 --> 29:07.658
-PROBABLE HEART ATTACK.

29:07.789 --> 29:08.747
-I'LL GET THE RESUSCITATOR.

29:08.877 --> 29:09.965
-LET ME TAKE OVER COMPRESSIONS.

29:10.096 --> 29:11.097
-EXCUSE ME.

29:12.098 --> 29:15.144
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

29:15.841 --> 29:18.234
-WHAT HAPPENED?
-LOOKS LIKE A FULL ARREST.

29:18.974 --> 29:20.410
-WE NEED A BACKBOARD.

29:20.541 --> 29:23.239
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

29:25.154 --> 29:28.114
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

29:28.244 --> 29:29.376
-IT'S THE RAG MAN.

29:29.506 --> 29:31.465
-HE'S GOT A NAME. MAX.

29:31.595 --> 29:33.119
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S
GET READY TO ROLL.

29:33.249 --> 29:35.034
READY, UP!

29:37.863 --> 29:39.299
ALL RIGHT, CONTINUE VENTILATION.

29:39.429 --> 29:41.431
I NEED TO GET HIM ON THE TRUCK.

29:43.607 --> 29:45.000
ALL RIGHT, RESUME CPR.

29:45.131 --> 29:46.959
-LOGAN, TAKE MY UNIT
BACK TO HEADQUARTERS

29:47.089 --> 29:48.134
AND DON'T FORGET MAX'S CART.

29:48.264 --> 29:49.570
-OKAY.

29:53.792 --> 29:58.057
-[SIREN BLARES]

30:02.801 --> 30:04.454
-LIFEGUARD: EVERYBODY READY?

30:04.585 --> 30:05.673
-KIDS: YEAH!

30:05.804 --> 30:07.022
-[BLOWS WHISTLE]

30:10.634 --> 30:15.814
-[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

30:46.888 --> 30:47.889
-COME ON!

30:57.159 --> 30:58.595
LET'S GO! COME ON, MANNY!

31:00.771 --> 31:02.034
LET'S GO, LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

31:03.644 --> 31:06.690
GOOD TIME, ALL RIGHT!
ATTA BOY, ATTA BOY!

31:06.821 --> 31:07.822
-THANKS, MAN.

31:08.823 --> 31:11.478
-LET'S GO, LET'S GO,
COME ON, KEEP IT COMING!

31:24.360 --> 31:25.840
-HOBIE: ALL RIGHT, WELL,
I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

31:25.971 --> 31:27.102
-GIRL: OKAY!

31:27.233 --> 31:28.756
-HOBSTER!

31:28.887 --> 31:29.931
-BYE, THANKS A LOT.

31:30.062 --> 31:31.367
-HEY, COME HERE.

31:32.847 --> 31:35.284
DID YOU, UH, GET YOUR
EARS PIERCED, HUH?

31:36.633 --> 31:38.461
I MEAN DID YOU REALLY WANNA
GET YOUR EARS PIERCED?

31:38.592 --> 31:40.202
-NO.

31:40.333 --> 31:41.160
-OR DID YOU GET A TATTOO
OR SOMETHING, LET ME SEE.

31:41.290 --> 31:42.465
-NO, NO. MAYBE, MAYBE.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.424
-LEVEL WITH ME,
OKAY, DID YOU GET

31:44.554 --> 31:45.991
ANYTHING PIERCED OR
TATTOOED IN THERE?

31:46.121 --> 31:47.731
-NO, DAD, NOT YET.

31:47.862 --> 31:51.170
-[SIGHS] COULD WE TAKE A
LITTLE WALK ON THE BEACH, HUH?

31:51.300 --> 31:52.388
COME ON.

31:57.654 --> 31:59.874
-REMEMBER WHEN I USED TO
CARRY YOU ON MY SHOULDERS?

32:00.005 --> 32:01.920
-YEAH, I USED TO LOVE IT.

32:02.050 --> 32:04.313
I REMEMBER I FELT
LIKE I WAS SO BIG.

32:05.358 --> 32:08.187
-YOU DON'T NEED ME FOR
THAT ANY MORE, NOW DO YOU?

32:08.317 --> 32:10.798
-NOT REALLY, BUT
THAT DOESN'T MEAN

32:10.929 --> 32:12.452
I DON'T NEED YOU
FOR OTHER THINGS.

32:14.149 --> 32:16.499
I JUST DON'T WANT YOU
TO PRESSURE ME INTO

32:16.630 --> 32:18.545
FOLLOWING IN YOUR FOOTSTEPS.

32:18.675 --> 32:20.547
-I WAS HOPING YOU'D
LEARN FROM MANNY

32:20.677 --> 32:22.679
ABOUT WANTING TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

32:22.810 --> 32:25.204
-WELL, I DID LEARN FROM
MANNY, I LEARNED A LOT.

32:26.248 --> 32:28.250
MANNY TAUGHT ME THAT
YOU SHOULD GO AFTER

32:28.381 --> 32:30.600
WHATEVER YOU WANT,
NO MATTER WHAT

32:30.731 --> 32:32.689
THE ODDS ARE OR
WHO'S AGAINST YOU.

32:35.301 --> 32:37.868
DAD, I KNOW WHAT I WANT.

32:40.132 --> 32:40.959
-WHAT?

32:41.089 --> 32:42.221
-MY TONGUE PIERCED.

32:45.572 --> 32:46.877
-YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT?

32:47.008 --> 32:48.618
-NO, WHAT DO YOU
THINK, LIKE RIGHT HERE?

32:48.749 --> 32:50.664
-NO, NO WAY, IT'S
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

32:50.794 --> 32:53.580
-DAD. I WANT IT AND THERE'S
NOTHING YOU CAN DO TO STOP ME.

32:53.710 --> 32:55.060
-NO, I'M STILL YOUR
FATHER AND I'M TELLING YOU

32:55.190 --> 32:56.409
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

32:56.539 --> 32:57.497
-YEAH, BUT I'M STILL
FASTER THAN YOU.

32:57.627 --> 32:59.020
-YOU'RE NOT FASTER THAN ME!

33:29.398 --> 33:31.922
-C.J., I WAS ON MY WAY TO
THE HOSPITAL TO MEET YOU.

33:32.793 --> 33:34.403
-INEZ DROPPED ME OFF.

33:34.534 --> 33:35.578
-WHAT HAPPENED?

33:36.710 --> 33:37.928
-HE DIDN'T MAKE IT.

33:38.886 --> 33:39.930
-I'M SORRY.

33:44.022 --> 33:45.414
COME ON, LET'S GO.

33:52.160 --> 33:54.641
-I DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF HE HAS ANY FAMILY

33:54.771 --> 33:56.773
OR ANYONE TO TAKE CARE
OF FUNERAL ARRANGEMENTS.

33:57.383 --> 33:58.732
-MAYBE MITCH CAN FIND OUT.

34:00.516 --> 34:02.170
-WHAT AM I GONNA
DO WITH HIS CART?

34:02.910 --> 34:04.346
-WE'LL FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

34:05.043 --> 34:06.392
RIGHT NOW, I THINK I
SHOULD GET YOU HOME.

34:07.045 --> 34:09.569
TAKE A BATH, RELAX,
AND WE'LL DEAL

34:09.699 --> 34:10.786
WITH ALL THIS IN THE MORNING.

34:13.225 --> 34:14.356
-I JUST CAN'T HELP
THINKING THAT I

34:14.487 --> 34:16.010
COULD HAVE DONE SOMETHING MORE.

34:16.706 --> 34:18.969
-YOU TRIED, C.J.,
YOU BEFRIENDED HIM.

34:19.100 --> 34:20.797
THAT'S MORE THAN
ANYONE ELSE DID.

34:22.190 --> 34:23.061
COME ON.

35:06.495 --> 35:07.583
-♪ CASEY JEAN

35:09.498 --> 35:10.456
♪ WHERE YOU BEEN

35:11.848 --> 35:14.547
♪ I'VE BEEN WAITING
HERE FOR YOU ♪

35:19.813 --> 35:20.944
♪ CASEY JEAN

35:22.337 --> 35:23.643
♪ WHERE YOU BEEN

35:24.948 --> 35:27.603
♪ I'VE BEEN WAITING
HERE FOR YOU ♪

35:31.041 --> 35:32.521
-HOW DO YOU KNOW MY NAME?

35:33.696 --> 35:35.437
-♪ FABRIC OF HIS LIFE

35:36.438 --> 35:37.918
♪ WAS HIS LIFE

35:38.048 --> 35:40.138
♪ 'TIL THE PAIN AND THE STRIFE

35:41.313 --> 35:44.054
♪ CUT INTO HIS
HEART LIKE A KNIFE ♪

35:46.883 --> 35:49.495
♪ YOU CAME ALONG AND

35:49.625 --> 35:51.279
♪ MADE RIGHT FOR THE WRONG

35:51.888 --> 35:54.413
♪ AND HE WAS LONGING
TO LIVE LONGER ♪

35:55.283 --> 35:57.242
♪ YOU MADE HIM STRONGER

35:58.547 --> 35:59.592
♪ NOW HE'S GONE

36:00.288 --> 36:02.072
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN YOU'VE
BEEN WAITING FOR ME?

36:07.600 --> 36:09.515
-♪ FABRIC OF HIS LIFE

36:10.429 --> 36:11.821
♪ IT WAS HIS LIFE

36:12.953 --> 36:13.954
♪ YOU WERE THE WIFE

36:15.216 --> 36:16.783
♪ HE NEVER HAD

36:16.913 --> 36:18.785
♪ BUT ALWAYS DREAMED OF

36:20.613 --> 36:22.571
♪ HERE BY THE SEA

36:23.268 --> 36:25.357
♪ HIS LEGACY

36:25.487 --> 36:27.359
♪ WAS LEFT TO ME

36:28.186 --> 36:30.318
♪ TO LEAVE TO YOU

36:30.927 --> 36:32.973
♪ SO YOU CAN HAVE ALL ♪

36:35.105 --> 36:37.891
♪ THAT YOU'VE EVER DREAMED OF

36:39.806 --> 36:41.199
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN
HIS LEGACY WAS

36:41.329 --> 36:43.679
LEFT TO YOU TO LEAVE TO ME?

36:49.424 --> 36:52.732
-[WHISPERS INAUDIBLY]

36:58.128 --> 36:59.826
-WHAT'S GOING ON,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36:59.956 --> 37:01.871
-C.J.: I DON'T KNOW, THIS
GUY WITH A GUITAR CAME BY

37:02.002 --> 37:03.786
AND TOLD ME THAT MAX LEFT
ME SOMETHING ON HIS CART.

37:03.917 --> 37:05.527
-WHAT? I'LL HELP
YOU LOOK FOR IT.

37:06.441 --> 37:07.442
-I DON'T KNOW.

37:10.097 --> 37:12.012
CODY, BE CAREFUL,
DON'T DAMAGE ANYTHING!

37:12.142 --> 37:13.013
-SORRY.

37:16.016 --> 37:17.060
-I FOUND IT!!

37:17.974 --> 37:19.106
-WHAT IS IT?

37:25.112 --> 37:27.157
-HIS LAST WILL AND TESTAMENT.

37:27.288 --> 37:28.768
-YOU'RE KIDDING, THE
GUY ACTUALLY HAD A WILL?

37:29.682 --> 37:31.423
-AND HE SAID HE LEFT
EVERYTHING TO ME.

37:31.553 --> 37:33.642
-AH, THE CART, HUH?

37:34.600 --> 37:35.775
SO WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO WITH IT?

37:36.689 --> 37:38.821
-IT SAYS HE HAD
MORE THAN A CART.

37:38.952 --> 37:41.346
-LIKE WHAT, GARBAGE BAGS
FULL OF SURPLUS MATERIAL?

37:50.616 --> 37:52.182
-COME ON, THIS
CAN'T BE FOR REAL.

37:52.792 --> 37:53.662
-WHAT IF IT IS?

37:54.968 --> 37:57.231
-HOW CAN IT BE, THE GUY WAS
A BUM WHO LIVED ON THE BEACH.

37:57.362 --> 37:58.928
-HE CHOSE TO LIVE HERE.

37:59.494 --> 38:01.148
AND HE THOUGHT HE WAS
LUCK TO BE ABLE TO.

38:01.714 --> 38:03.019
-IF HE HAD THIS MUCH MONEY,

38:03.150 --> 38:04.543
HE'D HAVE LIVED IN
A MALIBU MANSION.

38:04.673 --> 38:06.022
-DIDN'T HOWARD HUGHES
LEAVE HIS ENTIRE FORTUNE

38:06.153 --> 38:07.415
TO A GAS STATION
ATTENDANT WHO THOUGHT

38:07.546 --> 38:08.286
HE WAS A BUM AND
GAVE HIM A QUARTER?

38:09.287 --> 38:10.984
-CODY: FOUR MILLION DOLLARS?

38:12.855 --> 38:14.466
C.J.! WAIT UP!

38:20.472 --> 38:21.864
-CODY, WAIT UP!

38:23.344 --> 38:25.041
IS IT TRUE? DID C.J.
INHERIT FOUR MILLION

38:25.172 --> 38:26.782
DOLLARS FROM MAD MAX?

38:27.609 --> 38:29.394
-SHE INHERITED HIS MONEY.

38:29.524 --> 38:31.439
-I CAN'T BELIEVE HE HAD MONEY!

38:31.570 --> 38:33.833
I KNEW MAX, I MEAN, HE
LIVED IN A RAG CART.

38:34.660 --> 38:36.488
I USED TO TALK TO
HIM ALL THE TIME.

38:37.402 --> 38:38.968
-I GUESS HE JUST
LIKED C.J. BETTER.

38:40.622 --> 38:41.928
-YOU KNOW WE COULD USE SOME OF

38:42.058 --> 38:44.583
THAT MONEY TO PRODUCE OUR SHOW.

38:44.713 --> 38:47.716
DO YOU THINK C.J.
MAY WANT TO INVEST?

38:47.847 --> 38:49.152
-SHE GAVE ALL THE
MONEY AWAY, NEELY.

38:49.718 --> 38:50.676
-WHAT?

38:50.806 --> 38:52.460
-YEAH, TO HOMELESS SHELTERS.

38:53.548 --> 38:55.637
-SHE GAVE AWAY FOUR
MILLION DOLLARS?

38:56.986 --> 38:59.032
-[LAUGHS]

38:59.162 --> 39:00.599
-NEELY: WHAT?

39:00.729 --> 39:03.776
-4,000! MAX WROTE
TOO MANY ZEROS.

39:04.603 --> 39:08.084
-OH, I WAS BEGINNING TO
WORRY ABOUT C.J.'S SANITY.

39:08.215 --> 39:10.478
I MEAN, 4,000
TO A HOMELESS SHELTER,

39:10.609 --> 39:13.133
THAT'S GREAT, THAT'S
WONDERFUL OF C.J. BUT

39:13.263 --> 39:15.483
FOUR MILLION DOLLARS.

39:15.614 --> 39:18.747
-YOU KNOW, I BET IF IT
HAD BEEN FOUR MILLION

39:18.878 --> 39:20.575
SHE'D HAVE GIVEN THAT AWAY TOO.

39:21.620 --> 39:24.840
-AND THAT'S WHY YOU
LOVE HER SO MUCH, RIGHT?

39:24.971 --> 39:26.059
-WHAT CAN I SAY?

39:26.189 --> 39:27.800
-YOU'RE BOTH SICK PUPPIES.

39:29.671 --> 39:31.107
-OH, NEELY!

39:32.413 --> 39:36.025
-ALL RIGHT, LISTEN UP!
LIFEGUARDING IS
NOT FOR EVERYONE.

39:36.156 --> 39:39.942
BUT IF YOU STICK WITH
IT AND WORK REALLY HARD,

39:40.595 --> 39:43.424
YOU'LL HAVE THE MOST FUN
YOU EVER HAD IN YOUR LIFE.

39:43.555 --> 39:45.731
YOU CAN BE RESPONSIBLE
FOR A PERSON'S LIFE.

39:45.861 --> 39:48.298
YOU CAN SAVE SOMEONE'S LIFE.

39:49.299 --> 39:53.608
NOW, ONCE A LIFEGUARD,
ALWAYS A LIFEGUARD.

39:53.739 --> 39:56.524
NO MATTER WHERE YOU
GO OR WHAT YOU DO

39:56.655 --> 39:59.701
THIS EXPERIENCE WILL
ALWAYS BE A PART OF YOU

40:00.441 --> 40:02.400
AND WILL MAKE YOU
A BETTER PERSON.

40:03.531 --> 40:06.142
SO HAVE FUN, ENJOY THE WATER.

40:07.492 --> 40:08.493
MAKE THEM SUFFER.

40:08.623 --> 40:09.972
-YOU GOT IT.

40:10.103 --> 40:11.583
ALL RIGHT, IN THE
WATER UP TO YOUR KNEES,

40:11.713 --> 40:14.455
WE'LL START WITH A RUN
TO TOWER SIX AND BACK.

40:18.633 --> 40:22.681
-SO UH, COULDN'T
STAY AWAY, HUH?

40:23.638 --> 40:24.857
WHAT'S UP?

40:24.987 --> 40:26.293
-NOTHING MUCH.

40:26.424 --> 40:27.903
-OH NO.

40:28.556 --> 40:30.515
-[MUFFLED] DAD, WHAT'S WRONG?

40:31.646 --> 40:33.343
-SHOW ME YOUR TONGUE.

40:36.390 --> 40:39.045
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU, WHEN
ARE YOU GONNA GROW UP, HUH?

40:39.175 --> 40:40.960
-I'M SORRY...

40:41.090 --> 40:43.571
I DIDN'T OFFER YOU
A GUMBALL, DID I?

40:46.139 --> 40:49.969
-[LAUGHS] THAT'S VERY FUNNY.

40:50.099 --> 40:53.625
-GOT YOU, DIDN'T I?
-I'LL GET YOU BACK, JUST
WAIT, I'LL GET YOU BACK.

40:53.755 --> 40:54.887
-HEY DAD, WAIT A MINUTE.

40:55.017 --> 40:56.541
-WHAT?

40:56.671 --> 40:57.672
-I...

41:00.022 --> 41:01.546
I BET YOU KNOW.

41:01.676 --> 41:02.677
-I KNOW.

41:14.994 --> 41:19.215
-[THEME MUSIC]
